        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 2:57PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cahaba Heights, or over Mountain Brook. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Birmingham, Hoover, Vestavia Hills, Homewood, Mountain
Brook, Irondale, Indian Springs Village, Inverness, Cahaba Heights,
Five Points South, The Summit, Lake Purdy, Brook Highland, U.A.B.
Campus, Greystone, Meadowbrook, Grants Mill Road Bridge, Birmingham
Zoo, Liberty Park, and Hoover Veterans Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
